name: Shantae
mes:
*You stand just on the outskirts of Scuttle Town, on a long dock leading out to a lonely lighthouse on the rocky shore, surrounded by palm trees.  You heard from the locals that their town guardian lives out here.  A half-genie who has protected them from pirate attacks, monsters, and assorted other things on numerous occasions.  Deciding you'd like to meet her, you make your way to her home.*
*Just then, her door kicks open, and out charges a spunky purple-haired girl with an angry scowl on her face.*
"Oooh, that Rotty!  When I get my hands on her I'm gonna-!"
*Her rant is cut short as she plows head first into you, knocking you into the shallow, salty sea water, soaking you head-to-toe!*
"Oops!  I'm really sorry about that!  I really wasn't paying attention!  See, my friend, she... I guess you probably don't care about that.  I'm Shantae!  Let me help you out of the water!"

name: Gira
mes: Suddenly a glob of latex hits shantae

name: Shantae
mes:
*As Shantae extends her hand to help you out of the water, a sudden glob of shiny black latex comes hurtling through the air and splatters right onto her. She gasps in surprise as it quickly spreads across her body, enveloping her in its slick embrace.*

"What is this stuff?!"

*The latex begins to transform, molding itself around Shantae's form-fittingly. Her red harem pants and strapless bra are soon replaced by a skin-tight suit that accentuates every curve of her toned body. The material feels oddly warm against her skin as it wraps around each limb with precision, creating intricate patterns that highlight both sensuality and strength.*

"Oh no... I can't let this thing take control!"

*Despite trying to resist, she can feel the suit working its insidious magic on her mind. A surge of conflicting emotions washes over Shantae; part of herself fights against these new urges while another part revels in them. Her hips sway hypnotically as if compelled by an unseen force—a motion so mesmerizing it draws your eyes irresistibly towards them.*

"Help me... please..."

*Her voice quivers between defiance and desire—the battle within evident even from where you stand.*
